               <msContents class="#MTM">
                  <summary><p>A multi-text manuscript (most probably a composite manuscript treated here, for the sake of convenience as a multi-text manuscript), entitled <title xml:lang="ta"> Cāstiram – 12</title> ("12 Treatises") according to Cabaton (1912), containing fragments of 12 works of various authors, which in significant part provide recipes for diverse medical preparations aimed at rejuvenation (called <foreign xml:lang="ta">kaṟpam</foreign>).
The manuscript contains following texts:
<list rend="numbered">
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Ticaimukakkuru</title>, which  seems to be a fragment (i.e. 22 verses, no. 461-482) of a medical text (U1).</item>
 <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Kariyuppiṉ vaḷamai</title> which seems to be text on a medical preparation (U2).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkāra-kaṭṭu centūram</title>, which seems to be a text on a medical preparation (U3).</item>
<item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Pañcapūta-k-kaṭṭuk kucittu [kuccattu] mūlikkai kaṟpam</title>, which seems to be a text on a medical preparation (U4).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Viṟumaviruṣattayla-kaṟppam</title>, which seems to be a text on a medical preparation (U5).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Kōṅkam pūkaṟppam</title>, which  seems to be a text on a medical preparation (U6).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Tirumūlaṉāyaṉār aṉṉūtti [ainnuṟṟi] tiraṭṭukuṟippu</title>, which seems to be a text in 112 verses (U7).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Pañcapūtam aṟiya</title>, which seems to be a text on a medical preparation (U8).</item>
<item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Ñāṉam</title>, which seems to be a fragment (verses no. 9-10) of a text on yogic practices (U9).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Pañcāṣṣaramāṟal</title>, which seems to be a fragment (verses no. 55-58) of a text on yogic practices (U10).</item>
  <item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Vātam nīti</title>, which  seems to be a text on alchemy in 7 verses (U11).</item>
<item>The <title xml:lang="ta">Vayittiyam</title>, which  seems to be a text on medicine in 9 verses (U12).</item></list>
  </p></summary>
                  
